(luteal) phase of the menstrual cycle?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Corpus luteum secretes progesterone","Follicle stimulating hormone levels peak","Endometrial thickness decreases","Cervical mucus becomes thin and watery","Basal body temperature decreases"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring the luteal phase, the \u003Cstrong\u003Ecorpus luteum secretes progesterone\u003C/strong\u003E which prepares the endometrium for potential implantation by maintaining endometrial thickness. This phase is characterized by:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIncreased progesterone levels\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMaintained oestradiol levels\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThickening of the endometrium\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIncreased endometrial vascularity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIncreased basal body temperature\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFollicle stimulating hormone levels peak\u003C/strong\u003E during the follicular phase, prior to ovulation. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eendometrial thickness\u003C/strong\u003E actually increases during the luteal phase. \u003Cstrong\u003ECervical mucus becomes thin and watery\u003C/strong\u003E during the late follicular phase near ovulation. \u003Cstrong\u003EBasal body temperature\u003C/strong\u003E increases during the luteal phase due to the thermogenic effect of progesterone.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The corpus luteum produces progesterone during the luteal phase to prepare the endometrium for potential implantation","The endometrium thickens and becomes more vascular during the luteal phase","The luteal phase is characterized by increased progesterone and maintained oestradiol levels"],"references":["Hawkins SM, Matzuk MM. The menstrual cycle: basic biology.